Note & Install & Build
===============
Note:
  1. DIR827A1_GPL105.tar.gz include toolchain source code. 

Environment: 
	1. HostOS: Fedora Core 8 full installation.
	2. Update or install intltool
		(1). ~#sudo yum install intltool.i386
				 Please press "Y" and "enter" to proceed.
Install:
	1. Building the image.
		(1). Copy the DIR827A1_GPL105.tar.gz into /home/trunk directory
		     use following commands.
			~#tar -zxvf DIR827A1_GPL105.tar.gz
		(2). You will get "ubicom-distro-3.0" directory.
			~#cd /home/trunk/ubicom-distro-3.0
		(3). Unpack toolchain
			~#mkdir toolchain
			~#cd toolchain
			~#tar zxvf ../ubicom32toolchain-2011-05-28-platform.tar.gz
			~#cd ../
		(4)~#make menuconfig
  ¢x ¢x --- ******** General settings **********                                                                                                         ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x     Distro (uClinux)  --->                                                                                                                       ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x     Root file system (initramfs)  --->                                                                                                           ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x [*] Run distro menuconfig                                                                                                                        ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x --- ******** Upgrade Identity settings **********                                                                                                ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x (Unknown - BOARD) Application Identity String (up to 31 chars)                                                                                   ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x --- ******** Bootloader settings **********                                                                                                      ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x     Board (IP8100_DIR857.brd)  --->                                                                                                              ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x     LPJ (ultra8k.lpj)  --->                                                                                                                      ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x [*] Use pre-build ultra binaries                                                                                                                 ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x [ ] Enable Profiler                                                                                                                              ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x [*] Enable U-Boot                                                                                                                                ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x ---                                                                                                                                              ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x     Reset to defaults                                                                                                                            ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x     Load an Alternate Configuration File                                                                                                         ¢x ¢x
  ¢x ¢x     Save Configuration to an Alternate File    
          --please select <Exit>.
          
          Do you wish to save your new Ubicom Distro configrartion?
          --please select the <Yes>.

       b.uClinux Distribution Configuration:
            Vendor/Product Selection ----> 
         ---Selection the Vendor you wish to target
            Vendor(Ubicom)-->Ubicom
         ---Selection the Product yor wish to target
            products(DIR857NA3)-->DIR857NA3
         
         --->please select <Exit>.
         
         Do you wish to save your new kernel configrartion?
          --please slect the <Yes>.
         
         than if it shows "Process anyway? (N/y/?)", please press the 'enter' directly.
         
		(5)~#make
		(6). After make successfully, you will get the image file "DIR-827_upgrade.bin"
		     in "ubicom-distro-3.0/bin"
	2. Update the new firmware by web interface provided by device.
	3. You got your specific image now.
